      "id": "1l6kuvln8",
      "questionNumber": 2,
      "questionText": "<p>The spin only magnetic moment of the complex present in Fehling's reagent is __________ B.M. (Nearest integer).</p>",
      "options": [],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "tests-for-aldehyde-and-ketones",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": " In the complex present in Fehling's reagent, $\\mathrm{Cu}^{+2}$ ion is present.\n<br/><br/>\nSo, spin only magnetic moment\n<br/><br/>\n$$\n=\\sqrt{1(1+2)}\n$$\n<br/><br/>\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n& =\\sqrt{3} \\simeq 2 \\mathrm{~B} . \\mathrm{M}\n\\end{aligned}\n$$",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
